feedback:
Hello. One of my main stresses right now is my wife. She is a home health aide (CNA) and she usually has a lot of work in clients home. Since the Covid-19 crises, she is almost never called to work so she is not making income. She also has a lot of loans and bills so this is causing me stress. I'm trying to help her by using some of my retirement funds, and this is one of my main stress points in this whole crises. We live in the Boise area and it seems the outbreak has not been too bad here, at least we are fortunate in that respect. 
Also, since we live in the USA, you probably now healthcare is terrible here in the sense of how expensive it is even with insurance so we are trying very hard not to get the virus.
